This paper proposes a technique for improving the efficiency of gating in neural network models, specifically LSTM and highway networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing tasks such as speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of activation functions such as sigmoid, hyperbolic tangent, and rectified linear unit, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning models, suggesting that it could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper focuses on improving efficiency, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
